    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Vocabulary: Phone",
          "arabic": "مفردات: تليفون"
        },
        "text": "The word for 'phone' or 'telephone' in Egyptian Arabic is 'تليفون'. It's a loanword from English.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "تليفون",
            "english": "phone / telephone",
            "transliteration": "telefoon"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Asking for a Phone Number",
          "arabic": "كيف تسأل عن رقم التليفون"
        },
        "text": "To ask for someone's phone number, you combine 'رقم' with 'تليفون' and the possessive suffix '-ك' (ak/ik for male/female) for 'your'. So, 'رقم تليفونك كام؟' (raqam telefoonak kām?) means 'What is your phone number?' (to a male). For a female, it's 'رقم تليفونكِ كام؟' (raqam telefoonik kām?).",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "رقم تليفونكَ كام؟",
            "english": "What is your phone number? (male)",
            "transliteration": "raqam telefoonak kām?",
            "diacriticalNotes": "The kasra on 'كَ' (ak) changes to 'كِ' (ik) for a female."
          },
          {
            "arabic": "رقم تليفونكِ كام؟",
            "english": "What is your phone number? (female)",
            "transliteration": "raqam telefoonik kām?",
            "diacriticalNotes": "The kasra on 'كِ' (ik) changes to 'كَ' (ak) for a male."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Vocabulary: Passport & ID Card",
          "arabic": "مفردات: باسبور وبطاقة"
        },
        "text": "When traveling, you'll need to know words for important documents like 'passport' (باسبور) and 'ID card' (بطاقة). 'باسبور' is a loanword. 'بطاقة' is the general word for card, commonly used for ID.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "باسبور",
            "english": "passport",
            "transliteration": "basboor"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "بطاقة",
            "english": "ID card / card",
            "transliteration": "baṭaqa"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
