            "english": "What is your ID number? (female)",
            "transliteration": "raqam baṭaʾtik kām?",
            "diacriticalNotes": "The kasra on 'كِ' (ik) changes to fatḥa 'كَ' (ak) for a male."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Combining Politeness with Questions",
          "arabic": "جمع الأدب مع الأسئلة"
        },
        "text": "Always remember to add 'من فضلك' (please) to make your requests more polite. For example, 'من فضلك، رقم تليفونكَ كام؟' (min faḍlak, raqam telefoonak kām?) means 'Please, what is your phone number?' (to a male).",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "من فضلكِ، عنوانِك إيه؟",
            "english": "Please (to female), what is your address?",
            "transliteration": "min faḍlik, ʿunwānik ēh?"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
